Timavus, a small river at the head of the Adriatic between Trieste and Aquileia. For the last mile os its course it sinks through fissured limestone underground: and it is said that at times the sea comes rushing through the limestone and floods the land above the outlets. This is clearly what Vergil means to describe in 245—6.
